1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE

•  There are two separate sub‐structures:

   •  Left “House” Structure
      –  Consists of two blocks stacked in one column:
         1)  A red arch as the base  
         2)  An orange pitched‐roof block on top  

   •  Right “Gate/I‐Shape” Structure  
      –  Six blocks arranged in three “layers”:
         1)  Bottom layer: one long horizontal yellow block  
         2)  Middle layer: two vertical green columns on the left/right and two small cubes (red on top of blue) stacked between the green columns  
         3)  Top layer: one long horizontal yellow block  

•  Total Blocks Used: 8  
   –  2 in the “house”  
   –  6 in the “I‐shape”  

•  Layer Count:
   –  The house is effectively 2 layers.  
   –  The gate‐like structure is 3 layers tall (bottom bar, central cubes/columns, top bar).  

2)  SELECTING THE REQUIRED BLOCKS

Based on the dictionary image:

•  Red Arch (base of house) → Block #1  
  (It is the red arch oriented “right‐side up,” matching the house’s arch opening shown from the front.)  

•  Orange Roof (top of house) → Block #14  
  (This orange wedge/prism is oriented so that from the front it appears as a peaked roof.)  

•  Yellow Horizontal Bar (top & bottom of gate) → Block #9 (used twice)  
  (Block #9 is a short yellow rectangular prism oriented lengthwise left‐to‐right, matching the top and bottom bars.)  

•  Green Vertical Columns → Block #8 (used twice)  
  (Block #8 is the tall green rectangular prism oriented upright.)  

•  Red Cube (upper central cube) → Block #5  
  (A small red cube.)  

•  Blue Cube (lower central cube) → Block #4  
  (A small blue cube.)  

3)  ASSEMBLY ORDER

Below is a possible step‐by‐step sequence (place or “move” each block in the given order):

{
  Step1: "Move block with index 1"      // Red arch for house base
  Step2: "Move block with index 14"     // Orange roof on top of arch

  Step3: "Move block with index 9"      // Bottom yellow bar of gate
  Step4: "Move block with index 8"      // Left green column
  Step5: "Move block with index 8"      // Right green column
  Step6: "Move block with index 4"      // Blue cube (lower center)
  Step7: "Move block with index 5"      // Red cube (on top of blue)
  Step8: "Move block with index 9"      // Top yellow bar of gate
}
